The Online Alice
June 9 at 3:48 PM ·

Class of 2024 -

LHS summer school has been canceled due to the COVID-19 pandemic. If your student plans to take PE their Freshman year at LHS, during the regular school year, there is nothing you need to do.

If your student wants to earn one or both of their PE credits using Summer PE or a PE waiver, I’ve attached the policy for the class of 2024, only. This will need to be returned to Mrs. Tolliver by July 27, 2020. Please read carefully, and give me a call at 812-882-6168 if you have questions.

I hope all of you are well and we look forward to seeing you at Lincoln in August.

Mr. Combs

VCSC News
April 9 at 9:56 AM ·

Good morning all,

I certainly know that many of you are dealing with larger issues this morning from the storm. It is an E-Learning or counted day for education in the VCSC but this is secondary and quite frankly if it does not occur today, it does not occur.

Many of you are without power and this includes many of our staff members as well and they simply may not be available during the hours of 9AM to 2PM.

As we have learned with Covid-19, we have to be flexible. We just did not know that today that Covid-19 would become secondary for many of us and our attention would turn elsewhere and with this we must be flexible today and patient as we have too many people dealing with much larger issues than that of education and this is primarily related to the storm from last night.

Hopefully we will slowly start to return to what is the new normal for the time being, but today, education is far more secondary.

Hope you all are safe and with this, please stay safe!

Mr. Parsley

VCSC News
March 30 at 8:07 PM ·

WOW! What an amazing day. We thank you so much for your patience as we figure out our new normal with food distribution. It is so impressive to our staff, our families, our neighborhoods and our community rally around each other. We served out over 12,500 meals for the week in a two hour time period. Again, WOW! Thank you again for your patience, understanding, and cooperation as we continue to keep our students, our staff and community safe during this difficult time.

Franklin Remodel Walkthrough March Edition

Franklin Elementary

Please listen to this important announcement from Mr. Parsley.

If you have additional questions and/or concerns, please feel free to contact us anytime on our VCSC Helpline. (vcschelp@vcsc.k12.in.us or 812-882-6376)

Additional information will be released on our social media sites, our website and through SchoolMessenger.

Quick Points:
• Week of March 16th is Spring Break
• Week of March 23rd VCSC students will have educational opportunities available through eLearning.
• Week of March 30th VCSC students will be eLearning.
• Week of April 6th VCSC students return.
• Packets will be provided for those without eLearning capabilities.
• We are currently finalizing a plan for food service on the weeks of March 23rd and March 30th. Final information will be released early next week.

THESE PLANS ARE TENTATIVE AND SUBJECT TO CHANGE.

VCSC News
March 4 at 3:04 PM ·

VCSC Kindergarten Registration is HERE, with an early online option!

On Tuesday, March 10th from 4pm-6:30pm all VCSC elementary schools will be hosting kindergarten registration.

To register your child, please go to the school district that your child lives in. Yes, you will still need to go to the school on registration day EVEN IF YOU FILL OUT THE INFORMATION ONLINE.

To find what district you live in, please click on the link and enter your address.

Find my district: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-elementary-school-distric/home?fbclid=IwAR1vxmvX0_U75chcMjES5ho_Qxtymd0prqP3XL4ywdVCj9l7UeFmd5YcmRc

Please bring your child’s birth certificate, immunization records, and proof of address.

Your child must be 5 years old by August 1, 2020.

Online Kindergarten Registration: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-kg-reg-2033/home

We can’t wait to see you!

post_text:
Join us Friday, January 24, for Koala Day!

Bring $1.00 to donate and wear gray (like a Koala) on Friday, January 24 and all money raised will go to the Wildlife Victoria Organization to help shelter and rehabilitate animals that have been injured by the Australian wildfires.

All VCSC schools are participating!

Elementary school students can bring their donations to their teachers, middle schools students will have their donations picked up during lunch periods and high school students can drop theirs off in a bucket in the front office.

We hope our donation can make a difference in rebuilding the enclosures and habitats for the surviving animals.

Thank you for participating!
shared_text:
FRI, JAN 24
VCSC Koala Day
text:
Join us Friday, January 24, for Koala Day!

Bring $1.00 to donate and wear gray (like a Koala) on Friday, January 24 and all money raised will go to the Wildlife Victoria Organization to help shelter and rehabilitate animals that have been injured by the Australian wildfires.

All VCSC schools are participating!

Elementary school students can bring their donations to their teachers, middle schools students will have their donations picked up during lunch periods and high school students can drop theirs off in a bucket in the front office.

We hope our donation can make a difference in rebuilding the enclosures and habitats for the surviving animals.

Thank you for participating!
